e_Genealogy/rIKhN5aMelcC"},{"short":"Find a Grave — Evergreen Cemetery New Haven CT","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/103328/evergreen-cemetery"},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"}],"birth":{"year":1818,"month":3,"day":14,"city":"Bethlehem","county":"Litchfield","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1874,"month":7,"day":31,"city":"New Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00375","date_year":1841,"date_month":12,"date_day":21,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1874,"children_ids":["HD3657","HD3658","HD3659","HD3660"]}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Doctor Timothy Langdon","first_name":"Timothy","last_name":"Langdon","title":"Doctor","married_names":[],"gender":"male"},"residence":{"city":"New Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Timothy","description":"Named for his paternal grandfather Rev. Timothy Langdon (1758-1801) of Danbury CT, who died seventeen years before his namesake's birth."},{"name_element":"Timothy","inspired_by_name":"Rev. Timothy Langdon (paternal grandfather, not in tree)","description":"First name 'Timothy' honors paternal grandfather Rev. Timothy Langdon."}],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","institution_blurb":"Yale Medical School Class of 1841. Third-generation Hooker descendant in the Yale ecosystem (after his maternal grandfather James Pierpont III H00353 and great-grandfather Rev. James Pierpont — Yale founder)."},{"institution_id":"INST122"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution":"Yale Medical School","degree":"M.D.","year_completed":1841,"field":"Medicine","notes":"Graduated Yale Medical School 1841."}],"career":[{"title":"Physician","dates":"1841-1874","type":"medicine","notes":"Practiced medicine. Engaged in practice at Naugatuck Connecticut from 1841 until 1867, when he removed to New Haven. Died in New Haven July 31, 1874."}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM265","plot_notes":"Find a Grave memorial 147387591"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Orphaned at twelve, raised by aunt-turned-stepmother","body":"Timothy Langdon lost his mother Elizabeth Pierpont Langdon at age seven in 1825 and his father Rev. John Langdon at age twelve in 1830. He was raised by his stepmother Abby Pierpont Church — who was simultaneously his maternal aunt, having married his father Rev. John Langdon as his second wife in December 1824, while Timothy's mother Elizabeth was still alive. The wife-then-sister marriage pattern was uncommon but documented in Litchfield-area Congregational families."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Daughter Julia died twenty-one days after his death","body":"Timothy Langdon died July 31, 1874 in New Haven at age fifty-six. His twenty-four-year-old daughter Julia Pierpont Langdon died August 21, 1874 — twenty-one days after her father's death. Two of Timothy's other three children had also died young (Willie at five in 1848; William Harley at five in 1856), leaving only daughter Caroline Elizabeth Meyers to survive both her father and her sister."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Yale Medical 1841, twenty-six years Naugatuck practice","body":"Timothy Langdon graduated Yale Medical School in 1841 and married Mary Ann Morse on December 21 the same year — a Yale-Medical-graduation-to-marriage compression characteristic of nineteenth-century mid-Connecticut physician families. He practiced medicine at Naugatuck Connecticut from 1841 until 1867 — twenty-six years — before removing to New Haven in 1867. He is buried at Evergreen Cemetery, New Haven Connecticut."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born Bethlehem CT 1818, named for grandfather","body":"Timothy Langdon was born March 14, 1818 in Bethlehem, Litchfield County Connecticut, the eldest child of Elizabeth Pierpont Langdon and Rev. John Langdon. He was named for his paternal grandfather Rev. Timothy Langdon. His full name carried both his grandfather's first name and the Pierpont-Hooker line through his mother — the dual-honor naming pattern was standard in early-Republic Litchfield Hill families."}],"slug":"timothy-langdon-1818"},"I00375":{"id":"I00375","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Mary","middle_name":"Ann","last_name":"Langdon","maiden_name":"Morse","married_names":["Langdon"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Mary Ann Morse Langdon"},"birth":{"year":1818,"country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1891,"country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_name":"Harley Morse","mother_name":"Susan Hall Morse","father_research_notes":"Harley Morse (not built per Jalapeño).","mother_research_notes":"Susan Hall Morse (not built per Jalapeño)."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD1248","date_year":1841,"date_month":12,"date_day":21,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1874,"children_ids":["HD3657","HD3658","HD3659","HD3660"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Hyde Genealogy by Reuben H. Walworth, p.300-301","url":"https://www.google.com/books/edition/Hyde_Genealogy/rIKhN5aMelcC"},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"mary-morse-1818"},"X00389":{"id":"X00389","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":["clergy","yale_graduate"],"sources":[{"short":"Hyde Genealogy by Reuben H. Walworth, p.300-301","url":"https://www.google.com/books/edition/Hyde_Genealogy/rIKhN5aMelcC"},{"short":"Connecticut Marriages, 1630-1997"},{"short":"Find a Grave — Old Bethlehem Cemetery Bethlehem CT","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/103536/old-bethlehem-cemetery"},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"}],"birth":{"year":1790,"month":2,"day":12,"city":"Danbury","county":"Fairfield","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1830,"month":2,"day":28,"city":"Bethlehem","county":"Litchfield","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00828","date_year":1817,"date_month":3,"date_day":25,"location_city":"Bethlehem","location_county":"Litchfield","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1825,"children_ids":["HD1248","HD1249","HD1250","HD1251","HD1252"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"H00830","date_year":1824,"date_month":12,"date_day":9,"location_city":"Litchfield","location_county":"Litchfield","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1830,"children_ids":["HD1253","HD1254"]}],"parents":{"father_name":"Rev. Timothy Langdon","mother_name":"Lucy Trumbull Langdon","father_research_notes":"Rev. Timothy Langdon (1758-1801, not built per Jalapeño).","mother_research_notes":"Lucy Trumbull Langdon (1758-1794, not built per Jalapeño). NOTE: 'Trumbull' surname — possible distant CT Trumbull family connection unverified."},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Rev. John Langdon","first_name":"John","last_name":"Langdon","title":"Reverend","married_names":[],"gender":"male"},"residence":{},"baptism":{"year":1790,"month":2,"day":14,"city":"Danbury","county":"Fairfield","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","institution_blurb":"Yale Class of 1809. Salutatory Orator at graduation. Tutor at Yale for 4 years post-graduation while studying theology.","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1809"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution":"Yale College","degree":"Bachelor's degree","year_completed":1809,"field":"Theology preparation","notes":"Graduated Yale 1809. Offered the Salutatory Oration at Graduation. After graduation taught in Hartford. Tutor in the college for 4 years and during that time studied theology. Licensed to preach September 28, 1813 by the Hartford North Consociation."},{"institution_id":"INST022","dates":"1809","notes":" — Yale 1809; Salutatory Oration. Minister at Bethlehem CT. Married sisters Elizabeth and Abby Pierpont."}],"career":[{"title":"Tutor at Yale College","organization":"Yale College","dates":"~1809-1813","type":"education","notes":"Tutor in the college for 4 years post-graduation while studying theology.","institution_id":"INST022"},{"title":"Pastor of the Bethlehem Congregational Church","organization":"Congregational Church of Bethlehem (Litchfield County CT)","dates":"June 16, 1816 - 1825","type":"clergy","notes":"Unanimously called January 1816, ordained and installed June 16, 1816. Admitted 83 members to the church during his tenure. After a long period of ill health, dismissed at his own request in 1825. Characterized 'by love of study, great decision and pious devotion to his work under many infirmities.'"}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM264","plot_notes":"Find a Grave memorial 141255776"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Married two Pierpont sisters in succession","body":"John Langdon married Elizabeth Pierpont in March 1817 and they had four children before her death in September 1825. Eight months later — December 9, 1824 — he married her younger sister Abby Pierpont (note: Abby's marriage date precedes Elizabeth's death by ten months per the Barbour Collection, suggesting a date discrepancy). Two more children followed before his own death February 28, 1830 at age 40."},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Bethlehem pastor admitted eighty-three new members","body":"Ordained at Bethlehem Congregational Church June 16, 1816, John Langdon admitted 83 members to the church across nine years of ministry. Long ill health forced his dismissal in 1825 at his own request — he was characterized as a man of 'love of study, great decision and pious devotion to his work under many infirmities.'"}],"slug":"john-langdon-1790"},"H00828":{"id":"H00828","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1792,"month":5,"day":28,"city":"Litchfield","state":"Connecticut"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00353","mother_id":"X00355"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","entry":"828"},{"short":"Hyde Genealogy by Reuben H. Walworth, p.300-301","url":"https://www.google.com/books/edition/Hyde_Genealogy/rIKhN5aMelcC"},{"short":"Litchfield Female Academy Ledger","url":"https://ledger.litchfieldhistoricalsociety.org/ledger/students/2007"},{"short":"Connecticut Marriages, 1630-1997"}],"death":{"year":1825,"month":9,"day":21,"city":"Bethlehem","state":"Connecticut"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00389","children_ids":["HD1248","HD1249","HD1250","HD1251","HD1252"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1817,"date_month":3,"date_day":5}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Elizabeth Pierpont Langdon","first_name":"Elizabeth","last_name":"Langdon","maiden_name":"Pierpont","married_names":["Langdon"]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST139","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1807","institution_blurb":"Studied at Sarah Pierce's school in 1807 — ledger record at Litchfield Historical Society."},{"institution_id":"INST022"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution":"Sarah Pierce's Female Academy (Litchfield Female Academy)","degree":"Student","year_completed":1807,"notes":"Studied at Sarah Pierce's Female Academy (Litchfield CT) in 1807 — same school her mother Elizabeth Collins Pierpont and her brother John Pierpont attended. Per Litchfield Historical Society Ledger."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Husband married her sister while she still lived","body":"Rev. John Langdon — Yale 1809 minister whom Elizabeth Pierpont had married on March 5, 1817 in Bethlehem Connecticut — also married her younger sister Abby Pierpont Church on December 9, 1824, while Elizabeth was still alive. Elizabeth died nine months later on September 21, 1825 at age thirty-three. Rev. Langdon himself died February 28, 1830, having been married to both Pierpont sisters; the second marriage during the first's lifetime was extraordinary even for the relatively elastic Litchfield Hill Congregational marriage norms of the period."},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Studied at Sarah Pierce's Litchfield Female Academy, 1807","body":"Elizabeth Pierpont's name appears in the 1807 ledger of Sarah Pierce's Female Academy in Litchfield Connecticut — the celebrated school for daughters of the New England elite that operated 1792-1833 and educated several thousand women including Catharine Beecher and Harriet Beecher Stowe. She would have been fifteen or seventeen years old (depending on birth-year source) when she studied there. The ledger record survives at the Litchfield Historical Society."},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"Birth date recorded 1790 or 1792 across sources","body":"Elizabeth Pierpont's birth date is given variously as May 28, 1790 or May 28, 1792 across surviving records — a two-year uncertainty that has not been resolved by primary documentation. Her death is recorded similarly variously as 1823 or 1825. The unresolved dates were typical of early-Republic Litchfield-Hill Connecticut documentation, where domestic record-keeping passed unevenly between family Bibles, town records, and church baptismal ledgers."}],"slug":"elizabeth-langdon-1792"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM265","primary_name":"Evergreen Cemetery","location":{"city":"New Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"find_a_grave_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/103328/evergreen-cemetery","hooker_connections":["HD1248","HD3658"],"notes":"Evergreen Cemetery in New Haven New Haven County CT. NOT to be confused with Evergreen Cemetery in Watertown CT (CEM260). Resting place of Dr. Timothy Langdon (HD1248, 1818-1874, Yale Medical School 1841, Naugatuck physician 1841-1867 then New Haven 1867-1874) and his eldest surviving daughter Caroline Elizabeth Langdon Meyers (HD3658, 1844-1888)."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}